  <section>
    <h2>Unit 1 & 2 Vocabulary</h2>
    <ul style="text-align:left;">
      <li><b>Network:</b> A group of connected computers or devices that share information.</li>
      <li><b>Protocol:</b> Rules that allow devices to communicate across the Internet.</li>
      <li><b>IP Address:</b> A unique number given to each device on the Internet.</li>
      <li><b>Bandwidth:</b> The amount of data that can be sent through a connection.</li>
      <li><b>Algorithm:</b> A step-by-step process computers use to solve problems or make decisions.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>My Topic: Social Media Algorithms</h2>
    <p>Social media algorithms decide what content you see on platforms like Instagram, TikTok, and YouTube.  
    They track what you like, comment on, and share ‚Äî then recommend similar posts.  
    This makes your feed feel more personalized, but it can also create <b>filter bubbles</b> where you only see content you already agree with.  
    Understanding algorithms helps us use social media in smarter and healthier ways.</p>
  </section>

